BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:\n        <p>How pleasant it is when the people of tech come together in unity!</p>\n<p>Free admission. Food will be provided!</p>\n<p>After a year of talking about it\, we’re finally doing it: a chill summer cookout for everyone in Baltimore tech. No booths\, no buzzwords — just food\, sun\, and a mic for any group that wants to say hi.</p>\n<p>Participating groups</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Code Collective</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Baltimore Node Makerspace</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Baltimore Tech</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Brady UX</strong></li>\n<li><strong>DevOps Columbia</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Blk Tech Connect</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Baltimore Indie Game Devs</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>In the case of inclement weather\, the event will occur at Mount Vernon Marketplace.</p>\n        \n        <p><b>Event Link:</b> <a href="https://www.meetup.com/code-collective/events/307426667/">https://www.meetup.com/code-collective/events/307426667/</a></p>\n        \n        
DTEND:20250628T190000Z
LOCATION:Wonderground Park\, 409 E Lanvale St\, Baltimore\, MD 21202\, Baltimore\, MD us
DTSTART:20250628T170000Z
SUMMARY:Tech Unity Cookout
UID:6f8bc8cb-0dbd-4938-a0d6-b2c96ab9bd5d@6f8b.org
URL:https://www.meetup.com/code-collective/events/307426667/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:\n        <p>The 2025 Baltimore Neighborhood Economics Lab is a powerful\, day-long experience focused on Building a Just Economy in Uncertain Times. This convening brings together entrepreneurs\, neighborhood leaders\, organizers\, funders\, and policymakers from across the city and region to explore bold\, community-rooted strategies for sustaining and growing our local economies\, especially in the face of today’s economic and political uncertainty. Through interactive labs\, thought-provoking panels\, storytelling\, and solution design\, we will delve into the real challenges and creative opportunities surrounding capital access\, shared ownership\, local production\, youth leadership\, and emotional well-being. Together\, we’ll imagine what’s possible when we center equity\, care\, and collaboration in the work of building vibrant neighborhood economies. We invite you to be part of this space—not just to listen\, but to contribute\, co-create\, and connect.</p>\n        \n        <p><b>Event Link:</b> <a href="https://form.jotform.com/251063812795157">https://form.jotform.com/251063812795157</a></p>\n        \n        
SUMMARY:Baltimore Neighborhood Economics Lab
UID:5099692c-397c-4c5f-9a14-ac7e76821871@5099.org
URL:https://form.jotform.com/251063812795157
END:VEVENT
