END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:\n        <p>This month\, we will be meeting at RegionAle for happy hour and game night. This casual\, recurring happy hour is for both new and seasoned Baltimore technologists interested in connecting with fellow tech enthusiasts and a diverse group of awesome people. Come grab a drink\, plays some games and catch up!</p>\n<p>Stay tuned on all Baltimore Tech Meetups on our new <a href="https://www.instagram.com/baltimoretechmeetup/">Instagram - Baltimore Tech Meetup</a> or on Slack - <a href="http://baltimoretechslack.com/">Baltimore Tech Meetup</a>.</p>\n<p>Date: May 22nd 2025\nLocation: RegionAle - 2400 Boston St. Suite 120\, Baltimore\, MD 21224\nTime: 6:00pm to 8:00 pm</p>\n<p>### A few logistical details:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>We start at 6 PM. It usually lasts for a few hours - come and go when works for you.</li>\n<li>There is free parking in the parking lot in front.</li>\n<li>By attending\, all participants commit to upholding and being subject to our <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ctYtmK0_q16rm7Vk3hdBkC6o_4MQZ_148bEKLR9JoCE/edit?usp=sharing">Code of Conduct</a>.</li>\n<li>By attending\, participants also acknowledge and grant permission for the use of photographs they may appear in for promotional material by the organizers or sponsors. If you would like to rescind this permission\, please contact us directly.</li>\n</ul>\n        \n        <p><b>Event Link:</b> <a href="https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-tech/events/307783720/">https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-tech/events/307783720/</a></p>\n        \n        
DTEND:20250523T000000Z
LOCATION:RegionAle\, 2400 Boston St Suite 120\, Baltimore\, MD us
DTSTART:20250522T220000Z
SUMMARY:The #BaltimoreTech Happy Hour and Game night!
UID:5d51ce02-746f-47bc-b9e8-1b4bca5087ef@5d51.org
URL:https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-tech/events/307783720/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:\n        <p>Come join us for the Baltimore Indie Game Devs potluck picnic at BIG member Allen Lambert's house in Marriottsville just west of Baltimore. This picnic is for all local game devs in the Baltimore-Washington area. Allen will be manning the grill\, and there will be outdoor games as well as tabletop games to play.</p>\n<p>If you'd like to bring something to the potluck\, please add it in the Comments section.</p>\n<p>Notes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This is a NO ALCOHOL event.</li>\n<li>In the event of rain\, we may postpone this event.</li>\n<li><strong>We'll send the street address to RSVP'd attendees one week before the picnic and the day before the picnic. Please send a message to Allen Lambert or Tony Li if you'd like the address sooner.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n        \n        <p><b>Event Link:</b> <a href="https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-indie-game-developers-group/events/307582133/">https://www.meetup.com/baltimore-indie-game-developers-group/events/307582133/</a></p>\n        \n        
DTEND:20250621T210000Z
LOCATION:Crows Foot Road\, Crows Foot Rd\, Maryland\, MD us
